Known gaps for next sprint
- `frontend/app/(public)/donate/page.tsx` is still a prototype form and has not been wired to the real create donation flow.
- `frontend/app/(public)/campaigns/[id]/page.tsx` still sends users to separate support pages instead of offering a campaign-aware integrated support flow.
- `frontend/app/organization/transparency/page.tsx` is read-only; there is no manual transparency authoring or management flow yet.
- Login is unified by email/password and redirects by returned backend role; there is still no dedicated role chooser for sign-in because backend already resolves the role from the account.
- There is still no end-to-end test coverage; backend tests now cover permission helpers and campaign create/publish ownership, but broader endpoint coverage is still thin.
- Read-side access for organization-specific draft listings may need a dedicated authenticated endpoint later if the team wants a real organization campaign management screen.

Recommended next sprint order
1. Build the real public donation flow and reconnect campaign detail CTA to it.
2. Integrate campaign-aware support actions directly into campaign detail.
3. Add supporter and organization profile edit flows.
4. Decide and implement the next transparency step beyond read-only logs.
5. Add direct regression tests for the enriched dashboard endpoints and seed flow.

